Heat oven to 425 degrees F. Place Simply Potatoes(R) in single layer on 15x10x1-inch baking pan. Drizzle with oil; sprinkle with salt. Gently turn Simply Potatoes(R) to coat evenly with oil. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, turning occasionally, until Simply Potatoes(R) are crisp and golden brown. Meanwhile, cook ground beef and onion in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat until beef is browned. Drain grease. Reduce heat to low; add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until heated through. To serve divide potatoes evenly onto 4 dinner plates. Top potatoes with 1/4 of meat mixture, 1/4 cup cheese, 1/4 cup tomatoes and 1 tablespoon pickles.